<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Get a YouTube Data API Key</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0e1116;
    --panel: #161b22;
    --panel-border: #262c36;
    --text: #e6e9ef;
    --text-dim: #9aa4b2;
    --accent: #4f8cff;
    --accent-dim: #274a86;
    --code-bg: #0a0d12;
    --mono: "SFMono-Regular", Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
    --sans: "Inter", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .wrap {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 56px 24px 120px;
  }

  header.page-head {
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(79, 140, 255, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-dim);
    padding: 5px 10px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 34px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 16px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .progress-rail {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    background: rgba(14, 17, 22, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    padding: 14px 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    z-index: 10;
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .progress-rail .dot {
    flex: 1;
    height: 4px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--panel-border);
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .progress-rail .dot .fill {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    height: 100%;
    width: 0%;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: width 0.1s linear;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    padding: 32px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
  }

  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .step-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .step-body h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 4px 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .step-body p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .step-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  a.link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent-dim);
  }
  a.link:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }

  code, .kbd {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #d7dee8;
  }

  .img-slot {
    margin-top: 16px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    background: var(--panel);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .img-slot img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .callout {
    margin-top: 14px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    background: rgba(224, 169, 82, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(224, 169, 82, 0.35);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #f0d6a8;
  }

  .callout .icon { flex-shrink: 0; }

  .callout.danger {
    background: rgba(224, 90, 82, 0.08);
    border-color: rgba(224, 90, 82, 0.35);
    color: #f0b3ab;
  }

  .callout.success {
    background: rgba(87, 189, 122, 0.08);
    border-color: rgba(87, 189, 122, 0.35);
    color: #a7e0bb;
  }

  footer {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    h1 { font-size: 27px; }
    .step { gap: 14px; }
    .step-num { width: 30px; height: 30px; font-size: 12px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav class="progress-rail" aria-hidden="true">
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
  <span class="dot"><span class="fill"></span></span>
</nav>

<div class="wrap">

  <header class="page-head">
    <span class="eyebrow">Setup guide</span>
    <h1>Getting a YouTube Data API v3 key</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      A quick walkthrough for generating your own API key from Google Cloud Console,
      so you can start pulling data from YouTube in your project.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Open the YouTube Data API v3 page</h2>
      <p>
        Go straight to
        <a class="link" href="https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/youtube.googleapis.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/youtube.googleapis.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Sign in</h2>
      <p>If you aren't signed in already, sign up or log in with your Google account to continue.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Accept the Terms of Service</h2>
      <p>Check the box agreeing to the terms of service, then click <span class="kbd">Agree and continue</span>.</p>
      <div class="img-slot">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Cra-Z-Gaming/VUS/main/Tutorials/YT-API-Key/1.Agree-and-continue.PNG" alt="Agree to terms of service and continue">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Enable the YouTube Data API v3</h2>
      <p>Make sure your project is selected at the top, then click <span class="kbd">Enable</span>.</p>
      <div class="img-slot">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Cra-Z-Gaming/VUS/main/Tutorials/YT-API-Key/2.Enable-YT-Data.PNG" alt="Enable YouTube Data API v3">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Go to Credentials</h2>
      <p>
        Head to
        <a class="link" href="https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials" target="_blank" rel="noopener">console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">6</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Create an API key</h2>
      <p>
        On the top, click <span class="kbd">Create credentials</span>, then select <span class="kbd">API key</span>.
      </p>
      <div class="img-slot">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Cra-Z-Gaming/VUS/main/Tutorials/YT-API-Key/3.Create-API.PNG" alt="Create credentials then API key">
      </div>
      <p>
        Open the <strong>Select API restrictions</strong> dropdown, scroll down, then check/select
        <strong>YouTube Data API v3</strong>. Click <span class="kbd">Create</span>.
      </p>
      <div class="img-slot">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Cra-Z-Gaming/VUS/main/Tutorials/YT-API-Key/4.Select-restrictions.PNG" alt="Select API restrictions dropdown">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">7</div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <h2>Copy your key</h2>
      <p>Copy the key by clicking the copy icon, or select it manually.</p>
      <div class="img-slot">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Cra-Z-Gaming/VUS/main/Tutorials/YT-API-Key/5.Copy.PNG" alt="Copy your new API key">
      </div>
      <div class="callout">
        <span class="icon">⚠️</span>
        <span>Paste your key somewhere safe — a password manager or private notes file works well.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="callout danger">
        <span class="icon">🔒</span>
        <span>If anyone gets access to your key, it may stop working soon if it's used in unintended ways — treat it like a password.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="callout success">
        <span class="icon">✅</span>
        <span>Done! You may now use your new key.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  (function () {
    const fills = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.progress-rail .dot .fill'));
    const total = fills.length;

    function updateProgress() {
      const doc = document.documentElement;
      const scrollTop = doc.scrollTop || document.body.scrollTop;
      const scrollHeight = doc.scrollHeight - doc.clientHeight;
      // Guard against pages shorter than viewport
      const ratio = scrollHeight > 0 ? Math.min(Math.max(scrollTop / scrollHeight, 0), 1) : 1;

      const progressInDots = ratio * total; // e.g. 3.4 out of 7

      fills.forEach((fill, i) => {
        const dotProgress = Math.min(Math.max(progressInDots - i, 0), 1); // 0 to 1 per dot
        fill.style.width = (dotProgress * 100) + '%';
      });
    }

    window.addEventListener('scroll', updateProgress, { passive: true });
    window.addEventListener('resize', updateProgress);
    updateProgress();
  })();
</script>
</body>
</html>
